Key Thematic Areas and Emerging Trends
Pharmacology research spans basic mechanisms (receptors, signaling, pharmacokinetics/pharmacodynamics), drug discovery/development, clinical therapeutics, safety/toxicology, and pharmacoepidemiology. Current hot spots include:
AI, Machine Learning, and Computational Pharmacology: AI shortens drug discovery timelines (by 40–50% in some AI-native programs), enables in silico screening, molecular design, and predictive modeling (e.g., ADMET, quantum computing for tailored drugs). Model-informed drug development (MIDD) and mechanistic modeling are transforming efficiency. AI-designed drugs are advancing to clinical stages in oncology and fibrosis. 
