Precision and Personalized Medicine: Focus on pharmacogenomics, precision dosing (especially in oncology and renal impairment), biomarkers, and patient-specific responses. This includes integration of omics (genomics, proteomics, metabolomics) and real-world data (RWD/RWE) for better outcomes. 
frontiersin.org
Novel Modalities and Therapies: Antibody-drug conjugates (ADCs), radiopharmaceuticals, PROTACs (targeted protein degradation), cell/gene/RNA therapies, bispecifics, and large molecules. GLP-1 agonists and combinations for cardiometabolic disease exemplify large-population impact. Microbiome-based therapies are expanding beyond gut health. 
